MONTPELIER, Vt. (AP) — The Vermont Agency of Agriculture, Food & Markets has announced $500,000 in federal grant funds available to boost the state’s specialty crop industries.Specialty crops are defined as fruits, vegetables, tree nuts, horticulture crops and nursery crops, the agency said. Grants are available to producers for marketing and promotion, research and development, expanding availability and access to such crops, and addressing local, regional, and national challenges for producers, the agency said. Funding is also available to create or strengthen producer associations and cooperatives that serve specialty crop businesses. The agency will do an information session webinar  for all prospective applicants on Jan. 27. Pre-applications must be submitted by Feb. 27. A review committee will then pick top-ranking projects and invite them to submit full applications, the agency said.